                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.506/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Collier</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-09-14T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1927—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Your telegram No. 129, September 12, noon. The Department can perceive no
                    good basis for a protest against the provisions of the insurance law. See
                    Department’s telegram number 31, August 8, noon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
